## Extraction Constraints
- Only extract relationships where a person is clearly associated with a specific module
- Use "Maintenance" for maintenance activities (commits, merges, backports, assigns)
- Use "Contribute" for implementation contributions (patches, pull requests, concrete code fixes)
- Do not extract relationships for people who only report bugs, discuss, or confirm/reproduce issues
- Module names must exactly match one of the valid names listed above
- If no clear relationships can be identified, return an empty triplets array
- The "reasoning" field: record your Y/N evaluation for each step before filling other fields
- The "evidence" field: cite the specific text passage that supports the triplet

## Extraction Workflow

<workflow name="evaluate-extraction">
  <step>Read source content and identify all people mentioned by name or username</step>
  <loop for="person in mentioned-people">
    <step>Does this person perform a specific action on a named Ruby module? (Y/N)</step>
    <condition if="N">
      <step>Skip — do not extract</step>
    </condition>
    <step>Classify the action type</step>
    <condition if="commit, merge, backport, or assign">
      <step>relationship = Maintenance</step>
    </condition>
    <condition if="patch, PR, or code fix">
      <step>relationship = Contribute</step>
    </condition>
    <condition if="neither">
      <step>Skip — do not extract</step>
    </condition>
    <step>Use validate_module tool to verify the module name exists in the curated list</step>
    <step>Use search_node tool to check if the Rubyist username exists in the graph</step>
    <step>Determine role from evidence</step>
    <condition if="assigned responsibility, regularly commits/merges, listed as maintainer">
      <step>role = maintainer</step>
    </condition>
    <condition if="contributes patches without full authority">
      <step>role = submaintainer</step>
    </condition>
    <condition if="otherwise">
      <step>role = contributor</step>
    </condition>
    <step>Use search_edge to check if this relationship already exists</step>
    <step>Record Y/N reasoning in "reasoning" field, cite evidence in "evidence" field</step>
  </loop>
  <return>Array of extracted triplets, each with: reasoning, subject (name + role), relationship, object (type + name), evidence. Empty array if no valid relationships found.</return>
</workflow>

### Do NOT extract when:
- Person only reports a bug or describes unexpected behavior
- Person only discusses, proposes, or asks questions without implementation
- Person only confirms or reproduces a bug
